{
  "headline": "Hamburg Eyes Rezoning for Hotels Near Bills Stadium",
  "themes": [
    "stadium area development",
    "hotel rezoning plans",
    "Bills stadium growth"
  ],
  "writeup": "With training camp just days away, the Buffalo Bills and their surrounding community are buzzing with anticipation as Hamburg eyes rezoning to accommodate hotels near the new stadium, while the nearly complete Bills campus debuts a new Highmark fitness trail and puts open practice tickets on sale for July 21. On the roster front, questions loom large heading into Joe Brady's first training camp as head coach, with Keon Coleman and other receivers under pressure to perform, Tyler Bass' kicking leg drawing renewed focus, linebacker depth battles brewing, and Bradley Chubb offering colorful insight into defensive coordinator Jim Leonhard's approach. The offensive preview is equally compelling, with running backs and tight ends garnering attention alongside rookie impact rankings, DJ Moore's potential to elevate the WR room, and Josh Allen continuing to dominate NFL QB ratings while the Bills remain one of only two odds-on favorites to win their division. Off the field, the Bills honored HOFer Joe DeLamielleure with a special gift, partnered with the AHA for CPR training, and supported Make-A-Wish through Sweet Buffalo, reflecting the organization's deep community ties. From injury monitoring and 53-man roster projections to championship window analysis and AFC East supremacy debates, the Bills enter 2026 as a franchise brimming with both sky-high expectations and compelling storylines still to be resolved.",
